# Local: copy to ".env" and fill in your key from https://web3forms.com
# Production: .env is NOT uploaded to git — you MUST set the same variable on your host
# BEFORE running "npm run build" (Vite bakes VITE_* into the JS at build time).
#
# Netlify: Site settings → Environment variables → Add VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY → Redeploy
# Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Add for Production → Redeploy
# Cloudflare Pages: Settings → Environment variables → Production → Redeploy
# GitHub Actions: Repository → Secrets → Actions → add secret, use in workflow env for build step
#
# If the form works on localhost but not on your live URL, the key was missing at build time,
# OR Web3Forms may block some free subdomains — use a custom domain or see web3forms.com/docs troubleshooting.
VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=
